{
  "name": "Sneak Attack",
  "type": "feat",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>Beginning at 1st level, you know how to strike subtly and exploit a foe's distraction. Once per turn, you can deal an extra [[/damage 1d6]] damage to one creature you hit with an attack if you have advantage on the attack roll. The attack must use a finesse or a ranged weapon.</p><p>You don't need advantage on the attack roll if another enemy of the target is within 5 feet of it, that enemy isn't &amp;Reference[condition=incapacitated], and you don't have disadvantage on the attack roll.</p><p>The amount of the extra damage increases as you gain levels in this class, as shown in the Sneak Attack column of the Rogue table.</p></div>",
      "chat": ""
    },
